postcontent:
For Sale: I have a DPMS .22LR AR-15 with Aero Precision Lower and 5 Magazines.  The upper is a flat top with front sight post (see picture.) Includes a black Magpul MBUS flip-up rear sight.  Less than 200 rounds through it.  Upper is an aluminum receiver, not the plastic that you normally see.  This is NOT a conversion unit, meaning this upper was meant for .22LR, and the barrel has the proper 1x16 twist to stabilize the .22LR cartridge.

The lower is an Aero Precision Lower Receiver. This lower has always been used with this upper, so only 200 rounds.  It is NOT a "blemish" model.  Also, this is a standard lower receiver, meaning you can pair it with any standard AR-15 upper in a different caliber and it will work just fine.  It does NOT have to be used only with a .22LR upper, as many of the .22 rifles do.

Lower comes with a Gen 2 Falcon Ergo Grip, black Magpul CTR stock, and a JP Enterprises 3.5 trigger spring.  Buffer tube kit is an ATI mil-spec.

Magazines I believe are Black Dog.  One is a 10 round, two 15 rounds, and two 25 rounds.

Two notes-it comes equipped with the standard bolt catch, but I've found that it doesn't do a great job with the .22LR bolt. The bolt does lock back on an empty mag, but the bolt catch doesn't engage.  Not really a big deal, and with a standard 5.56 upper, it will work just fine. It also comes with a dust cover that I couldn't get to stay closed.  To me these are minor issues.  I am selling the gun because I could use the money right now.

title: For Sale/Trade:  J. P. Sauer & Sohn .32ACP or 7.65 German (nazi) pistol $200.00 OBO ot TRADE
postcontent: The Sauer 38H or often just H was a small semi-automatic pistol made in Nazi Germany from 1938 until just after the end of World War II by J. P. Sauer & Sohn, then based in Suhl, Germany. The "H" in the model number denotes "hammerless"—the pistol uses an internal hammer. Marked as 7.65 cal. It was produced between 1939–45. The model 38H was used by German armed forces such as the Luftwaffe, as well as police forces in numbers nearly equal to the Walther PPK. THIS PISTOL HAS THE German Wehrmacht MARKS (MILITARY) !The Sauer 38H was produced for military, police, and the commercial market. I believe it to be the third variation according to the serial number. It is a nice piece of NAZI history from WW2. It is a used pistol that is around 74 years old. The finish is not great but the bore is in excellent shape.  I was told it shoots and is accurate but I have not shot it.  The grips are not correct but they sell repros on ebay for $34.00................................I am looking for a nice modern pistol or revolver to trade even for. Any caliber. Just let me know........e-mail with trade offers ............................or $200.00 . Must be an Ohio resident 21 or older legally able to purchase a handgun. PLR-16
The PLR-16 is a gas operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in 5.56 mm NATO caliber. It is intended to be the ideal Silhouette shooting and hunting pistol. The rifling is 1 turn in 9 inches, right hand twist. The PLR-16 has a conventional, long-stroke gas-piston operation and utilizes the proven Johnson/Stoner breech locking system. The rear sight is adjustable for windage. The front sight is similar to an AR-15 style rifle, and adjustable for elevation. An integrated MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail will accept a multitude of standard accessories. The muzzle is threaded 1/2-28 TPI to accept standard attachments such as a muzzle brake or flash hider. Except for the barrel, bolt, sights, and mechanism, the PLR-16 pistol is made entirely of high-impact glass fiber reinforced polymer.
